# Connectivity Fix Plan

## Goal
Fix `net::ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED` errors by ensuring the backend server is running and accessible to the frontend client.

## Proposed Changes

### Client
- [ ] Update [vite.config.js](file:///d:/project/Fittness%20tracking%20website/client/vite.config.js) to include a proxy for `/api` to avoid CORS issues and simplify environment configuration.
- [ ] (Optional) Update client API configuration to use relative paths if a proxy is correctly set up, or ensure the base URL matches the server's port.

### Server
- [ ] Ensure the server listens on the expected port (likely 5000).
- [ ] Add a `start` script or ensuring `npm run dev` is executed to run the backend.

## Verification
- [ ] Run `npm run dev` in the `server` directory.
- [ ] Run `npm run dev` in the `client` directory.
- [ ] Open the application in the browser and verify that login/register requests succeed (or at least hit the server).
